caption: Charming neighborhood bistro setting.  Tasty homemade soups, eclectic menu, daily drink specials, reasonably priced house red and white wines.  Great staff.

Excellent little hidden gem in Gold Coast. Would def go back again. Service is very friendly. The food was made with love! And the vibes were immaculate. Used to: do my homework here at odd hours of the night, linger here for hours writing in my sketch-journal or playing board games with friends (before when they used to open til 2AM back in the day). Nice vibe in a vintage Chicago style hotel right on the corner of Goethe and Dearborn.

They also have full bar and bunch wine racks so if you come here for an evening meal there is plenty of drinks to chose from.

Best, most cozy spot in the Gold Coast. Well-priced and delicious with a fresh, new menu every night. The burger and pizza are favorites but the artichoke ravioli and the Chinese noodle soup are just some of my personal favorites. The staff feels like family, we know them now, and Janet is the kindest, Most generous owner. We come here several times a week because there is just nothing better on a Tuesday night than a cozy Third Coast meal, and it’s just a nice treat and so much better and easier than cooking. 5 stars.

Used to hang out in the back where I constantly wrote in my sketch-journals, read many books, had dates, drank coffee with friends so much it was rather excessive. When you grew up in a city where hibernating better part of the year was normal you always would find a place where everybody knows your name, and they're always glad you came :) sometimes you'd meet people from out of town here like a pair of Wisconsin girls I met and we'd simply play Monopoly for kicks which was fun, spontaneous, memorable. A neighborhood staple and Gold Coast hideaway from tourists and suburbanites that frequent the other places nearby. A good place to meet friends when everyone is craving something different with a menu that ranges from salads to all day breakfast. The bacon here is notable - thick and lean. Specials change regularly including daily drink specials. A limited but thoughtful selection of bottled beers, wines, and cocktails. No fried food here. Though it's something similar to an upscale coffee shop, the menu isn't basic and the atmosphere is casual, music is always nice, staff is attentive and most have been there a long while. Portions are generous without being obnoxious and sides are great - baby spinach ceasar, sauteed brussel sprouts are part of a long list. I love breakfast here - Mexican steak and eggs, Italian omelettes, crisp hash browns, anything served with bacon. Filled pastas are a good call for evening meals. If you're craving breakfast at night, ask for the menu and they're happy to accommodate you.

I love this place. Quaint and cute little cafe with great service and nice size menu and portions! However, I'm rating this 3 starts because of the food itself. I have been there many times in the last 3 months and each time my food is really cold. Often my eggs are barely warm. Butter does not melt on toast, pancakes or French toast- at all. I have asked for things to be warmed up and they come out roughly the same temp. Again, this is a great place but just some small changes to food delivery would make it perfect!
